race.description: Strathmore Community Bank Imperatriz Sprint Handicap
race.comment: TONKIN (9) looks beautifully placed here. She's a fast mare who won well fresh as favourite before trying hard in a strongly run 1100m down the Flemington straight, giving away weight to a male winner. Now she plummets 5.5kg and comes back to 1000m around a bend, all of which are positives. BEAST MODE (7) had the blinkers applied and went like a rocket around the 955m here last time out, scoring by 2.75 lengths. Have to respect again down in the weights. DON'T HOPE DO (8) is racing very consistently off a strong win at Caulfield last time. Back to 1000m is a slight niggle but he'll be staying on strongly. MAJOR SHARE (5) comes into calculations following scratchings.
